TITLE: Defining a Table in FlatBuffers Schema
DESCRIPTION: Example of defining a table in FlatBuffers schema. Shows various field types, default values, and attributes. Tables are the main way of defining objects in FlatBuffers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/flatbuffers/blob/master/docs/source/schema.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
table Monster {
  pos:Vec3;
  mana:short = 150;
  hp:short = 100;
  name:string;
  friendly:bool = false (deprecated, priority: 1);
  inventory:[ubyte];
  color:Color = Blue;
  test:Any;
}
```

