TITLE: Object-Based API Usage in C++
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the object-based API for FlatBuffers, showing how to unpack a buffer into objects and pack them back.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/flatbuffers/blob/master/docs/source/languages/cpp.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: cpp
CODE:
```
// Autogenerated class from table Monster.
MonsterT monsterobj;

// Deserialize from buffer into object.
GetMonster(flatbuffer)->UnPackTo(&monsterobj);

// Update object directly like a C++ class instance.
cout << monsterobj.name;  // This is now a std::string!
monsterobj.name = "Bob";  // Change the name.

// Serialize into new flatbuffer.
FlatBufferBuilder fbb;
fbb.Finish(Monster::Pack(fbb, &monsterobj));
```

