TITLE: Reading FlatBuffer Binary File in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to read a FlatBuffer binary file in Java. It imports necessary libraries, reads the file into a byte array, wraps it in a ByteBuffer, and uses it to create a Monster object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/flatbuffers/blob/master/docs/source/languages/java.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
import MyGame.Example.*;
import com.google.flatbuffers.FlatBufferBuilder;

// This snippet ignores exceptions for brevity.
File file = new File("monsterdata_test.mon");
RandomAccessFile f = new RandomAccessFile(file, "r");
byte[] data = new byte[(int)f.length()];
f.readFully(data);
f.close();

ByteBuffer bb = ByteBuffer.wrap(data);
Monster monster = Monster.getRootAsMonster(bb);
```

