TITLE: Table Definition in FlatBuffers
DESCRIPTION: Example of a table definition in FlatBuffers. Tables are variable-sized objects that use vtables for field access and support schema evolution through default values for missing fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/google/flatbuffers/blob/master/docs/source/internals.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
struct Monster : private flatbuffers::Table {
  const Vec3 *pos() const { return GetStruct<const Vec3 *>(4); }
  int16_t mana() const { return GetField<int16_t>(6, 150); }
  int16_t hp() const { return GetField<int16_t>(8, 100); }
